             was indicted for <rs id="t18310106-76-off432" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-off432" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-off432" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310106-76-cd433" type="crimeDate">25th of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-76-off432 t18310106-76-cd433"></join>, 16 lbs. weight of beef, value 7s., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18310106-76-victim716" type="victimName">
                           Thomas William 
                           Jones
                        <interp inst="t18310106-76-victim716" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310106-76-victim716" type="given" value="Thomas William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310106-76-victim716" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-76-off432 t18310106-76-victim716"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , his master
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-76-person717">
                  THOMAS 
                  WILLIAM JONES
               <interp inst="t18310106-76-person717" type="surname" value="WILLIAM JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-person717" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-person717" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was in my employ about twelve months, and had 15s. a week. On Christmas-day, I went into the loft with my son - I saw some hay behind the screen, and behind the hay were<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183101060038"></xptr>three pieces of beef - I wrote my initials on three pieces of paper and put them into the beef; this was between twelve and one o'clock; I left the beef there, and gave information to Vann - between two and three o'clock the prisoner went out with a bundle under his left arm, and in about three minutes, he was brought back with the beef which had the paper in it, as I had put it there; he said it was his first offence, and begged me to forgive him, having a wife and four children; he had but two pieces of beef into his apron, the other was still in the loft - I had cut the beef myself and put them on the board of my shop; the whole weighed 24 lbs.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-76-person718">
                  THOMAS 
                  VANN
               <interp inst="t18310106-76-person718" type="surname" value="VANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-person718" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-person718" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner come out of the shop, and followed him; I took him back with the parcel; there was a shirt or two, and a handkerchief in the bundle, and these two pieces of beef.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I acknowledge I had the two pieces, but not the third.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 33. <rs id="t18310106-76-verdict434" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-verdict434" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-76-verdict434" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               Recommended to Mercy by the Prosecutor
            </rs>.</p>
